#: src/import_hook.md:1 src/import_hook.md:213
msgid "Import Hook"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:3
msgid ""
"[maturin_import_hook](https://pypi.org/project/maturin-import-hook/) "
"provides a mechanism to automatically rebuild Maturin projects when they are "
"imported by Python scripts."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:6
msgid ""
"This reduces friction when developing mixed Python/Rust codebases because "
"edits made to Rust components take effect automatically like edits to Python "
"components do. Automatic rebuilding eliminates the possibility of Python "
"code using outdated rust components, which often leads to confusing "
"behaviour."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:10
msgid ""
"The import hook can be configured to activate automatically as the "
"interpreter starts or manually in individual scripts. Only Maturin packages "
"installed editable mode (`maturin develop` or `pip install -e`) are "
"considered by the import hook. When the build is up to date the overhead of "
"the import hook is minimal."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:14
msgid ""
"The hook has some additional features such as importing stand-alone `.rs` "
"files. See [Features](#features) for a complete list."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:17
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:19
msgid "Install the package with:"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:24
msgid "Then install it into the current virtual environment with:"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:28
msgid ""
"This will activate the hook automatically as the interpreter starts. This "
"command only has to be run once per virtual environment. To use `site "
"install`, ensure you have write access to `site-packages`. Using a [virtual "
"environment](https://docs.python.org/3/library/venv.html) is recommended "
"rather than installing into the system interpreter."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:34
msgid "The managed site installation can be removed with:"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:39
msgid ""
"To manually activate the import hook only for specific scripts instead of "
"installing into the virtual environment see [Manual Activation](#manual-"
"activation)."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:42
msgid "Basic Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:44
msgid ""
"The site installation can be customized. For example, to build in release "
"mode:"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:45
msgid ""
"```shell\n"
"$ python -m maturin_import_hook site install --args=\"--release\"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:48
msgid ""
"The `--args` option accepts `maturin develop` arguments. For more options "
"see `--help`."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:50
msgid ""
"The site installation can also be edited manually. Use `python -m "
"maturin_import_hook site info` to locate the `sitecustomize.py` file. See "
"[Install Arguments](#install-arguments) for a list of arguments to "
"`install()`."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:53
msgid ""
"To avoid unnecessary rebuilds caused by irrelevant file modifications, "
"create empty `.maturin_hook_ignore` files to manually ignore directories. "
"Several directories and file types such as `target/` and `*.py` are ignored "
"by default. If more customization is needed, see [Custom File Searching]"
"(#custom-file-searching)."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:57
msgid "CLI"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:59
msgid ""
"The package provides a CLI for managing the build cache and site "
"installation. For details, run:"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:65
msgid "`site (info | install | uninstall)`"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:66
msgid ""
"Manage import hook installation in [`sitecustomize.py`](#sitecustomize) of "
"the active environment."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:68
msgid "`install` options:"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:69
msgid ""
"`--force`: Whether to overwrite any existing managed import hook "
"installation."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:70
msgid "`--(no-)-project-importer`: Whether to enable the project importer."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:71
msgid "`--(no-)-rs-file-importer`: Whether to enable the rs file importer."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:72
msgid ""
"`--(no-)-detect-uv`: Whether to automatically detect and use the `--uv` flag."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:73
msgid "`--args`: The arguments to pass to `maturin`."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:74
msgid ""
"`--user`: whether to install into `usercustomize.py` instead of "
"`sitecustomize.py`."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:75
msgid "`cache (info | clear)`"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:76
msgid "Get info about the size and location of the build cache."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:77
msgid "Manage the build cache of the active environment."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:78
msgid "`version`"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:79
msgid ""
"Show version info of the import hook and associated tools. Useful for "
"providing information to bug reports."
msgstr ""

