msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:91
msgid "Importing multiple Maturin projects in the same script."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:92
msgid ""
"Importing stand-alone `.rs` files that use `PyO3` bindings (see [Import Rust "
"File](#import-rust-file))."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:93
msgid "`importlib.reload()` (currently unsupported on Windows)."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:94
msgid "Detecting edits to path dependencies at any depth."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:95
msgid ""
"Multiple environments with different interpreters using isolated build "
"caches."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:96
msgid ""
"Concurrent imports/builds from multiple scripts (useful for tools like "
"[`pytest-xdist`](https://pypi.org/project/pytest-xdist/))"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:97
msgid "Extensibility (see [Advanced Usage](#advanced-usage))."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:99
msgid "Manual Activation"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:101
msgid ""
"To activate the import hook in a single Python script, call `install()` at "
"the top of the script:"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:105
msgid "# Must come first. Not active for imports above.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:107
msgid "# An editable-installed Maturin project.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:109
msgid "# `foo/my_rust_script.rs` defines a pyo3 module.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:112
msgid ""
"The Maturin project importer and the Rust file importer can be used "
"separately:"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:122
msgid ""
"The import hook can be configured to control its behaviour (see [Install "
"Arguments](#install-arguments))."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:124
msgid ""
"The import hook is intended for use in development environments and not for "
"production environments, so any calls to `install()` should ideally be "
"removed (or disabled, see [Environment Variables](#environment-variables)) "
"before reaching production. This is another reason why the site installation "
"is convenient."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:129
msgid ""
"The hook remains active across multiple Python modules so a single "
"`install()` at the top of the main module is sometimes sufficient. This can "
"cause problems however, when the main module is not imported or not imported "
"first, such as in tests. `install()` can be called in each module but be "
"aware that each call replaces the previous settings."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:133
msgid ""
"Tip: If you want to use non-defaults across multiple modules you can create "
"a function like:"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:143
msgid "# your custom configuration here\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:147
msgid ""
"Then call `install_maturin_hook()` at the top of each module. This will "
"ensure the custom options are used everywhere without any code duplication."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:150
msgid "Import Rust File"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:152
msgid ""
"When a `.rs` file is imported, a Maturin project with [pyo3](https://pyo3."
"rs/) bindings will be created for it in the Maturin build cache and the "
"resulting library will be built and loaded."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:155
msgid "For example, `my_extension.rs`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:167
msgid ""
"The `#[pymodule]` must have the same name as the filename. The version of "
"`pyo3` is determined by `maturin new --bindings pyo3`."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:172
msgid "Environment Variables"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:174
msgid ""
"The import hook can be disabled by setting `MATURIN_IMPORT_HOOK_ENABLED=0`. "
"This can be used to disable the import hook in production while leaving "
"calls to `install()` in place."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:177
msgid ""
"Build files will be stored in an appropriate place for the current system "
"but can be overridden by setting `MATURIN_BUILD_DIR`. These files can be "
"deleted without causing any issues (unless a build is in progress). The "
"precedence for storing build files is:"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:181
msgid "`MATURIN_BUILD_DIR`"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:182
msgid ""
"(Each environment will store its cache in a subdirectory of the given path)."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:183
msgid "`<virtualenv_dir>/maturin_build_cache`"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:184
msgid "`<system_cache_dir>/maturin_build_cache`"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:185
msgid "e.g. `~/.cache/maturin_build_cache` on POSIX."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:187
msgid ""
"See the location being used with the CLI: `python -m maturin_import_hook "
"cache info`"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:189
msgid "Logging"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:191
msgid ""
"By default, the `maturin_import_hook` logger does not propagate to the root "
"logger. This is so that `INFO` level messages are shown without having to "
"configure logging (`INFO` level is normally not visible). The import hook "
"also has extensive `DEBUG` level logging that would clutter application "
"logs. So by not propagating, `DEBUG` messages from the import hook are not "
"shown even if the root logger has `DEBUG` level visible."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:196
msgid ""
"If you prefer, `maturin_import_hook.reset_logger()` can be called to undo "
"the default configuration and propagate the messages as normal."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:199
msgid ""
"When debugging issues with the import hook, you should first call "
"`reset_logger()` then configure the root logger to show `DEBUG` messages. "
"You can also run with the environment variable `RUST_LOG=maturin=debug` to "
"get more information from Maturin."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:205
msgid "'%(asctime)s %(name)s [%(levelname)s] %(message)s'"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:211
msgid "Background"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:215
msgid ""
"An [import hook](https://docs.python.org/3/reference/import.html#import-"
"hooks) is a class added to [sys.meta_path](https://docs.python.org/3/library/"
"sys.html#sys.meta_path) that is invoked by the Python interpreter whenever "
"it encounters an `import` statement (or import via other means). "
"`find_spec()` is called for each hook until one returns a `ModuleSpec` "
"indicating that it found the module. If a hook cannot handle a particular "
"import it returns `None`. Import hooks can be used to create modules on "
"demand (e.g. the `.rs` importer) or trigger side-effects with imports (e.g. "
"the project importer)."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:222
msgid ""
"[MaturinProjectImporter](https://github.com/PyO3/maturin-import-hook/blob/"
"main/src/maturin_import_hook/project_importer.py):"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:224
msgid ""
"Detects when an import corresponds to an editable installed Maturin project."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:225
msgid "Determines if the current build of the project is up to date."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:226 src/import_hook.md:233
msgid "Rebuilds the project if necessary."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:228
msgid ""
"[MaturinRustFileImporter](https://github.com/PyO3/maturin-import-hook/blob/"
"main/src/maturin_import_hook/rust_file_importer.py):"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:230
msgid ""
"Searches `sys.path` for an `.rs` file matching the import (e.g. for `import "
"foo.bar`, the hook will look for `foo/bar.rs` at each search path)."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:232
msgid ""
"Creates a temporary Maturin project for the `.rs` file or reuses the project "
"if it already exists."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:235
msgid ""
"The above steps are a simplification as supporting `importlib.reload()` "
"requires more complex logic. See [reloading.md](https://github.com/PyO3/"
"maturin-import-hook/blob/main/docs/reloading.md) for more details."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:238
msgid "Sitecustomize"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:240
msgid ""
"If a [sitecustomize.py](https://docs.python.org/3/library/site.html) file "
"exists in the `site-packages` directory of a Python installation it is "
"loaded automatically by the Python interpreter as it starts unless the `-S` "
"flag is passed to it. This makes `sitecustomize.py` a convenient place to "
"activate the import hook."
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:245
msgid "Advanced Usage"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:247
msgid "Install Arguments"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:249
msgid ""
"The arguments to `install()` are ([source](https://github.com/PyO3/maturin-"
"import-hook/blob/main/src/maturin_import_hook/__init__.py)):"
msgstr ""

#: src/import_hook.md:252
msgid ""
"\"\"\"\n"
"enable_project_importer: enable the hook for automatically rebuilding "
"editable installed maturin projects\n"
"\n"
"enable_rs_file_importer: enable the hook for importing .rs files as though "
"they were regular python modules\n"
"\n"
"enable_reloading: enable workarounds to allow the extension modules to be "
"reloaded with `importlib.reload()`\n"
"\n"
"settings: settings corresponding to flags passed to maturin.\n"
"\n"
"build_dir: where to put the compiled artifacts. defaults to "
"`$MATURIN_BUILD_DIR`,\n"
"    `sys.exec_prefix / 'maturin_build_cache'` or\n"
"    `$HOME/.cache/maturin_build_cache/<interpreter_hash>` in order of "
"preference\n"
"\n"
"force_rebuild: whether to always rebuild and skip checking whether anything "
"has changed\n"
"\n"
"lock_timeout_seconds: a lock is required to prevent projects from being "
"built concurrently.\n"
"    If the lock is not released before this timeout is reached the import "
"hook stops waiting and aborts.\n"
"    A value of None means that the import hook will wait for the lock "
"indefinitely.\n"
"\n"
"show_warnings: whether to show compilation warnings\n"
"\n"
"file_searcher: an object used to find source and installed project files "
"that are used to determine whether\n"
"    a project has changed and needs to be rebuilt\n"
"\n"
"enable_automatic_install: whether to install detected packages using the "
"import hook even if they\n"
"    are not already installed into the virtual environment or are installed "
"in non-editable mode.\n"
"\"\"\""
msgstr ""

